## 4. Testing the Integration

### Manual Testing Checklist

1. **Component Loads**
- [ ] Navigate to `/catalog` (or wherever OmniCatalog is mounted)
- [ ] Parts grid loads without errors
- [ ] Search works (type “pro” → results filter)
1. **Add to Cart - Happy Path**
- [ ] Click “Add to Cart” on a part with stock > 5
- [ ] Green toast appears: “Added [SKU] (5 units) to cart”
- [ ] Part appears in cart (check Zustand store or cart page)
- [ ] Price is correct (price × 5 / 100)
1. **Add to Cart - Out of Stock**
- [ ] Click “Add to Cart” on a part with stock = 0
- [ ] Button is disabled (visual feedback)
- [ ] No error toast (expected behavior)
1. **Add to Cart - Low Stock**
- [ ] Find a part with stock = 3 (below MOQ of 5)
- [ ] Click “Add to Cart”
- [ ] Red toast: “Only 3 unit(s) available. Minimum order: 5 units.”
1. **Quantity Selection (Bonus)**
- [ ] If you implement a quantity modal: ensure qty >= 5
- [ ] If qty < 5, show error or disable input

### Unit Test Example (Jest)

```typescript
// __tests__/OmniCatalog.test.tsx
import { render, screen, fireEvent, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';
import OmniCatalog from '@/components/OmniCatalog';
import { useCartStore } from '@/stores/cart';

// Mock fetch
global.fetch = jest.fn();

// Mock Sonner toast
jest.mock('sonner', () => ({
  toast: {
    success: jest.fn(),
    error: jest.fn(),
  },
}));

describe('OmniCatalog - Cart Integration', () => {
  it('adds part to cart with MOQ=5', async () => {
    const mockPart = {
      id: '1',
      sku: 'APHONE15-BATT',
      brand: 'Apple',
      stock: 10,
      price: 2999, // $29.99
      partType: { id: '1', name: 'Battery' },
      quality: { id: '1', name: 'OEM' },
      searchIndex: 'iphone 15 battery oem',
    };

    (global.fetch as jest.Mock).mockResolvedValueOnce({
      ok: true,
      json: async () => ({ success: true, parts: [mockPart] }),
    });

    render(<OmniCatalog />);

    await waitFor(() => {
      fireEvent.click(screen.getByLabelText(/add.*battery.*to cart/i));
    });

    // Assert: part was added with qty=5
    const state = useCartStore.getState();
    expect(state.items).toHaveLength(1);
    expect(state.items[0].quantity).toBe(5);
    expect(state.items[0].price).toBe(2999);
  });

  it('shows error toast when stock < MOQ', async () => {
    const mockPart = {
      id: '2',
      sku: 'APHONE15-SCREEN-LOW',
      stock: 3, // Below MOQ of 5
      // ... rest of part
    };

    // ... render and click ...

    await waitFor(() => {
      expect(toast.error).toHaveBeenCalledWith(
        expect.stringContaining('Only 3 unit(s) available')
      );
    });
  });
});
```

