## 6. Monitoring & Debugging

### Log Cart State

Add this hook to the component for debugging:

```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  const cartItems = useCartStore((state) => state.items);
  console.log('[OmniCatalog Debug] Cart items:', cartItems);
}, []);
```

### Check Zustand DevTools

Install Redux DevTools extension and add to your store:

```typescript
// /src/stores/cart.ts
import { devtools } from 'zustand/middleware';

export const useCartStore = create<CartStore>(
  devtools((set) => ({
    // ... store implementation ...
  }), { name: 'CartStore' })
);
```

Then open DevTools → Redux tab to inspect state changes.

-----

## 7. Rollout Checklist

Before deploying to production:

- [ ] Cart store exists and is type-safe
- [ ] Sonner installed and Toaster provider added
- [ ] `handleAddToCart` updated with validation logic
- [ ] Unit tests pass (cart add, validation)
- [ ] Manual testing: happy path + error cases
- [ ] Toast messages are clear and helpful
- [ ] Analytics event (if applicable) is firing
- [ ] Error handling for network/Zustand issues
- [ ] Accessibility: “Add to Cart” button aria-label is descriptive

-----

## 8. Future Enhancements

|Enhancement                                              |Effort|Benefit                              |
|---------------------------------------------------------|------|-------------------------------------|
|**Persistent Cart** (localStorage → server)              |Medium|Users don’t lose cart on reload      |
|**Batch Operations** (multi-select, add 10 parts at once)|High  |Power user feature                   |
|**Cart Item Editor** (change qty inline)                 |Low   |Better UX than deleting and re-adding|
|**Estimated Subtotal** (visible before checkout)         |Low   |Transparency, reduces surprises      |
|**Recent Searches** (saved to localStorage)              |Low   |Faster repeat orders                 |

